# C# simple properties: one line per property

When adding or editing **simple** auto-implemented properties (no custom accessor bodies, no `get =>` expression bodies), use a **single physical line** for the whole property declaration, including accessors.

## Do

```csharp
public Guid TenantId { get; set; }
public string? Name { get; init; }
public int Count { get; private set; }
AgentType AgentType { get; }
```

Keep optional attributes on the line(s) immediately above the property; the property line itself stays one line.

## Do not

Do not expand simple accessors across multiple lines:

```csharp
// Avoid
public Guid TenantId
{
    get; set;
}
```

## Adjacent properties: no blank line between

When two **consecutive** member lines are both simple one-line `{ get; set; }` auto-properties, **do not** put an empty line between them. This keeps DTOs and models compact while preserving a blank line before the next **different** member kind (method, nested type, field group, or a property that is not a simple `get; set;` line).

### Do

```csharp
public Guid TenantId { get; set; }
public Guid WorkspaceId { get; set; }
public string Name { get; set; } = null!;

public void EnsureValid()
{
    ...
}
```

### Do not

```csharp
// Avoid: blank line only between two adjacent simple get/set properties
public Guid TenantId { get; set; }

public Guid WorkspaceId { get; set; }
```

**Note:** `{ get; init; }` and `{ get; }` are **not** covered by the “collapse blanks” rule above—only `{ get; set; }` pairs are packed together. You may still use a blank line to separate those from each other or from `get; set;` lines if it helps readability.

## Scope

- Applies to `get;` / `set;` / `init;` **auto-properties only**.
- Does **not** apply when either accessor has a body (`get { return ... }`, `get =>`, `set { ... }`).
- Indexers, explicit interface implementations, and unusual modifiers follow normal C# formatting; if a property is too long for readability, prefer extracting types or using `required` / split lines on the **type** only when the team agrees—default remains one line for simple DTOs and models.

## Bulk fix

To re-normalize files after a bad merge, run from the repo root:

`python scripts/collapse_simple_properties.py`

That script:

- Collapses multiline blocks whose body is purely `get;`/`set;`/`init;` (plus optional one-line `[...]` attributes above the declaration).
- Removes blank lines between **adjacent** one-line `{ get; set; }` declarations.
